cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image reconstruction and deep learning-based methods for autofocusing and phase recovery. Additionally, it could also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories as it uses a convolutional neural network for image reconstruction. The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with holographic imaging, and neural networks (cs.NE) as it uses a deep learning approach.
